Let me start by saying i'd give this place 4 stars for the food alone. If you are looking for a killer grease ball burger with fresh cut fries, this is the place. The hospitality on the other hand makes me both sad and angry.  Angry because of how my co worker was treated. We would frequently go here and order 3-4 people's worth of food with each visit. The last time he went in to pick up food, while was he was waiting, the people behind the counter and the cooks began to ridicule his tattoos, as they were showing because it was a hot day. At first he thought they were joking but it continued. It continued to the point where they began questioning his up bringing, his beliefs and his morals. Again all this after he paid and was waiting for his food to cook. In a country were religious tolerance is supposed to be a thing why would your religion or lack of have anything to do with ordering and enjoying a burger.  Sad because none of us will ever step foot in this place again. You can have whatever beliefs you want but when you start chastising others for no good reason, others that are paying customers, then you won't be getting our business.
